148
00:11:54,487 --> 00:11:57,748
So I'm a Cape Verdean American. If you're completely unfamiliar with Cape Verde,

149
00:11:57,748 --> 00:12:04,669
there it is on the right hand side. It's a little tiny country off the west coast of Africa. Yes,

150
00:12:04,669 --> 00:12:12,411
that's Africa on the right. And I grew up in Massachusetts, very kind of far from Cape Verde,

151
00:12:12,411 --> 00:12:16,332
but nestled in one of the largest Cape Verdean populations in the country.

152
00:12:16,332 --> 00:12:19,793
And I've been making digital games off and on for 20 plus years.

153
00:12:20,732 --> 00:12:25,896
and I have a variety of experiences that have to do with the way that I've built games.

154
00:12:25,896 --> 00:12:30,739
But when I started making games, I think one of the most important things to note is that

155
00:12:30,739 --> 00:12:35,583
I was the only child in our subsidized housing project shown on the right with a computer.

156
00:12:35,583 --> 00:12:42,688
So it's a good example of what I've seen several game developers mention, which is that

157
00:12:43,547 --> 00:12:50,032
I, like the other game designers, and I'm refraining from giving their stories because I want you to read their stories and hear them directly from them,

158
00:12:50,032 --> 00:12:56,557
but 90% of my childhood friends owned or played a console game, but very few of them made games.

159
00:12:56,557 --> 00:12:59,940
They all played, but they didn't really make games.

160
00:13:00,380 --> 00:13:05,483
And so if you look at some of the data according to Pew Research, African-Americans are the most

161
00:13:05,483 --> 00:13:09,805
